Wrangling

Diamonds

Each of the following tasks can be accomplished by a statement of the form

diamonds %>% verb1( args1 ) %>% verb2( args2 ) %>% arrange(desc( args3 )) %>% head( 1 )

  1. Which color diamonds seem to be largest on average (in terms of carats)?
  diamonds %>%
    group_by(color)%>%
    summarise(avg.size=mean(carat))%>%
    arrange(desc(avg.size))%>%
    head(1)
## Source: local data frame [1 x 2]
## 
##    color avg.size
##   (fctr)    (dbl)
## 1      J 1.162137
  1. Which clarity of diamonds has the largest average table per carat?
  diamonds%>%
    group_by(clarity)%>%
    summarise(avg.table.per.carat=mean(table/carat))%>%
    arrange(desc(avg.table.per.carat))%>%
    head(1)
## Source: local data frame [1 x 2]
## 
##   clarity avg.table.per.carat
##    (fctr)               (dbl)
## 1    VVS1            141.4822

  1. What are the top 3 Second vote selections among people who voted for Betsy Hodges as their first choice?
  Minneapolis2013%>%
    filter(First=="BETSY HODGES")%>%
    group_by(Second)%>%
    summarise(nSecondVotes=n())%>%
    arrange(desc(nSecondVotes))%>%

  1. Which Precinct had the highest fraction of First vote selections marked as undervote? (To calculate the fraction, use mean(First == "undervote") in the argument to summarise().)
  Minneapolis2013%>%
    group_by(Precinct)%>%
    summarise(percent.undervote=mean(First == "undervote"))%>%
    arrange(desc(percent.undervote))%>%
    head(1)
